# Model assignments — operator-controlled routing

Production users **do not** pick LLM provider or model. Coop assigns models per feature.

## Source of truth

`src/config/featureModelAssignments.ts` — `COOP_FEATURE_MODEL_ASSIGNMENTS` and `resolveAssignedModelForUseCase()`.

| Feature | Provider | Model |
|---|---|---|
| Chat | OpenAI | gpt-4o-mini |
| Quick actions + integration chat | Anthropic | claude-sonnet-4-6 |
| /edit patches | OpenAI | gpt-5-mini |
| Autocomplete | Mistral | codestral-latest |

## Required wiring (all must stay connected)

1. **Settings UI** (`SettingsDetailViews.tsx` `ModelDetail`) — read-only assignment rows + On/Off badges; toggles only. **Never** add provider/model pickers to settings.
2. **Extension runtime** — `resolveRuntimeModelForUseCase()` in `CoopChatSession`; `resolveRuntimeAutocompleteModel()` in `completionRouter`.
3. **Config writes** — `stripUserModelPreferenceUpdates()` in `SecureApiClient.updateConfiguration` blocks `llmProvider` / `defaultModel` unless dev mode.
4. **Server enforcement** — `chatApi.ts` and `inlineCompletionApi.ts` override client model when `!config.allowUnapprovedProvider`.

## Dev mode only

`coopAI.devMode: true` may unlock runtime routing overrides via VS Code User settings (`coopAI.llmProvider`, `coopAI.defaultModel`). The settings webview must **never** show provider/model pickers.

## Tests

Run `npx tsx src/config/featureModelAssignments.test.ts` and `npm run test:autocomplete` after any change to model routing or Model & chat settings.

## Docs

Keep `website/content/docs/model-assignments.md` in sync with `COOP_FEATURE_MODEL_ASSIGNMENTS`.
